     C* FORCE (Chapter 27): self-authored equivalent of the manual's own
     C* Figure 298 (a primary NBR field controls how many secondary records
     C* FORCE routes to the next cycle; the manual's own worked example is
     C* garbled beyond reliable reconstruction in this project's OCR'd copy
     C* of the source, docs/ref/manual_text.txt). Primary FPRIM has 2 records:
     C* NBR=1 then NBR=0. Secondary FSEC has 2 records (values unused).
     C*
     C* If FORCE works, the single secondary read it forces lands strictly
     C* between the two primary records (PCNT==1 at that moment) -- ind60
     C* fires and sets RPGRET=1. Without FORCE, normal no-match-field
     C* selection always re-picks the still-available primary (priority 0)
     C* first, so both primary records are read back-to-back before any
     C* secondary record is ever touched; PCNT is already 2 by the time a
     C* secondary record is seen, ind60 never fires, and RPGRET stays 0.
     FFPRIM   IP  F    80              DISK
     FFSEC    IS  F    80              DISK
     IFPRIM       01
     I                                     1   2   0NBR
     IFSEC        02
     I                                     1   2   0SVAL
     C  01                 ADD  1         PCNT
     C  01                 Z-ADDNBR       CNT
     C  02       PCNT      COMP 1                        60
     C  60                 Z-ADD1         RPGRET
     C           CNT       COMP 0                    81
     C  81                 FORCEFSEC
     C  N81                FORCEFPRIM
